'''Nasal septum deviation''' is a common physical disorder of the [[Human nose|nose]], involving a displacement of the [[nasal septum]].

==Causes==
It is most frequently caused by [[Physical trauma|impact trauma]], such as by a blow to the [[face]].<ref name=metson>
