| publisher = McGraw-Hill Professional
| isbn = 0-07-144469-6}}
</ref> It can also be a [[congenital disorder]], caused by compression of the nose during childbirth.<ref name=metson/>  Deviated septum is associated with genetic connective tissue disorders such as [[Marfan syndrome]], [[Homocystinuria]]<ref>
